qas.question: Which city is the endpoint of I-26?
I-24 connects which two Tennessee cities?
Which interstate highway running north-south passes through Memphis?
Which interstate ends at a junction close to Dandridge, Tennessee?
What Tennessee cities are connected by I-269?

context: Interstate 40 crosses the state in a west-east orientation. Its branch interstate highways include I-240 in Memphis; I-440 in Nashville; I-140 from Knoxville to Alcoa and I-640 in Knoxville. I-26, although technically an east-west interstate, runs from the North Carolina border below Johnson City to its terminus at <a0_0>Kingsport<a0_0/>. I-24 is an east-west interstate that runs cross-state from <a1_0>Chattanooga to Clarksville<a1_0/>. In a north-south orientation are highways I-55, I-65, I-75, and I-81. Interstate 65 crosses the state through Nashville, while Interstate 75 serves Chattanooga and Knoxville and <a2_0>Interstate 55<a2_0/> serves Memphis. <a3_0>Interstate 81<a3_0/> enters the state at Bristol and terminates at its junction with I-40 near Dandridge. I-155 is a branch highway from I-55. The only spur highway of I-75 in Tennessee is I-275, which is in Knoxville. When completed, I-69 will travel through the western part of the state, from South Fulton to Memphis. A branch interstate, I-269 also exists from <a4_0>Millington to Collierville<a4_0/>.
